				<span class="postdetails">
					<br /><b>Joined:</b> Mon Sep 27, 2004 8:33 am<br /><b>Posts:</b> 2802
				</span>

			</td>
			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Even for an echo buffer of just $2000 bytes, you have less than a 1% possibility of it corrupting your final patch as it's executing, so you won't see it occur often. The fix is simple: set EDL to 0 initially, and then set it to the correct value just before/after restoring FLG. Not sure why you'd avoid this simple fix and have the loader fail occasionally for no obvious reason.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
