				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">It would be neat if SPC file rips were wrapped like almost all other ripped formats, where there is a standard way to get control back so you could upload a new song. It might not be that hard to write an automated program to at least determine what values must be written to the ports to cause re-entry to the IPL ROM (though some games might use a custom loader, and never re-enter the IPL ROM). These key values could be stored at some currently-unused offset in an SPC file.</div>

